1
00:00:17,199 --> 00:00:18,039
Let me ask you,

2
00:00:18,320 --> 00:00:20,199
those AH7s I told you
to sell off quietly,

3
00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:22,070
how did they end up
in Bai Han's hands?

4
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:23,039
I swear,

5
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:24,879
I didn't know it was him.

6
00:00:25,839 --> 00:00:27,039
He offered the highest price

7
00:00:27,080 --> 00:00:28,620
and didn't even ask to check the goods.

8
00:00:28,780 --> 00:00:29,500
He just told me

9
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,600
to drop them in a dumpster
at the abandoned building.

10
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:32,880
He seemed like he knew his stuff,

11
00:00:33,119 --> 00:00:34,000
so I sold it to him.

12
00:00:34,420 --> 00:00:36,700
I used the burner phone in the drawer
to contact him.

13
00:00:36,719 --> 00:00:38,600
Don't worry.
It can't be traced back to us.

14
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:40,880
The higher-ups want me

15
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:43,079
to track down the leak now.

16
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:45,540
What do you want me to do?
Investigate myself?

17
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:46,150
No, no.

18
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:47,920
Or should I just hand you over to them?

19
00:00:48,119 --> 00:00:48,600
No, no.

20
00:00:48,679 --> 00:00:49,399
Please don't.

21
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:18,359
Hello.

22
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:19,760
Tie Xin.

23
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:22,680
I have one day left
before our deadline.

24
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:25,319
How did the AH7s go missing?

25
00:01:25,719 --> 00:01:27,040
What have you found?

26
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,079
I'm close.

27
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:31,239
I've narrowed it down to three people.

28
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:38,400
Tie Xin?

29
00:01:39,359 --> 00:01:41,120
If you don't bring me

30
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,480
the thief in 24 hours,

31
00:01:43,239 --> 00:01:45,000
then as far as I'm concerned,

32
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:46,719
you're the thief.

33
00:01:47,159 --> 00:01:48,000
Got it.

34
00:01:48,319 --> 00:01:49,280
Loud and clear.

35
00:02:14,199 --> 00:02:14,759
Yes?

36
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:15,800
I know

37
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:19,039
you took our AH7.

38
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,360
The higher-ups want answers,

39
00:02:24,860 --> 00:02:26,560
and I need to give them an answer.

40
00:02:29,479 --> 00:02:30,800
Let's meet.

41
00:02:34,039 --> 00:02:34,639
Sure.

42
00:02:36,319 --> 00:02:37,039
Where?

43
00:02:37,380 --> 00:02:38,740
I'll text you the address.

44
00:03:15,919 --> 00:03:16,680
We

45
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,120
finally meet.

46
00:03:21,319 --> 00:03:22,439
You really came alone?

47
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:26,000
I came with nothing but good intentions.

48
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:28,780
What good intentions
are we talking about?

49
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:33,039
Thought I'd catch you
a little something,

50
00:03:33,719 --> 00:03:35,560
but turns out, there's nothing left

51
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,319
in Yong'an Village's river.

52
00:03:45,479 --> 00:03:47,199
There's something in that river,

53
00:03:47,759 --> 00:03:48,639
the River Spirit.

54
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,599
He only takes bad people.

55
00:03:52,439 --> 00:03:53,680
You sure you're not on his list?

56
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:58,960
Plenty of gods want me gone.

57
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:00,150
He'll have to get in line.

58
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,800
Let me take my shot then.

59
00:04:04,879 --> 00:04:06,439
Wait, wait, hold on!

60
00:04:06,719 --> 00:04:08,919
I really want to work with you.

61
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,919
Just give me a chance.

62
00:04:21,020 --> 00:04:21,720
Keep talking.

63
00:04:21,879 --> 00:04:24,800
Tie Xin is your enemy, right?

64
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:27,200
Well, he's been squeezing
the life out of me too.

65
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:29,279
To him, I'm nothing but a dog.

66
00:04:30,959 --> 00:04:32,360
But if you take him out,

67
00:04:32,879 --> 00:04:34,000
I get to move up.

68
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:36,800
Let's help each other.

69
00:04:37,399 --> 00:04:38,360
What do you want?

70
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:53,079
I won't ask for much.

71
00:04:54,079 --> 00:04:55,560
Just your dried fruit gift boxes.

72
00:04:56,540 --> 00:04:57,510
A truckload of it.

73
00:05:04,839 --> 00:05:05,639
Done.

74
00:05:10,319 --> 00:05:11,319
We do this face-to-face.

75
00:05:14,639 --> 00:05:15,279
Okay.

76
00:05:16,879 --> 00:05:17,600
Wait for my call.

77
00:05:22,439 --> 00:05:24,800
Tie Xin isn't an easy target.

78
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,270
I only get one shot at this.

79
00:05:27,279 --> 00:05:28,120
And so do you.

80
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,639
To make sure nothing goes wrong...

81
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:34,540
Have you got enough people for the job?

82
00:05:36,319 --> 00:05:37,720
Don't worry about that.

83
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,319
I don't.

84
00:07:06,267 --> 00:07:15,870
=The Embers=

85
00:07:17,122 --> 00:07:19,850
=Episode 16=

86
00:07:21,249 --> 00:07:24,020
=Chapter 4=
=Knowing Me=

87
00:08:15,519 --> 00:08:16,279
Liao Siyuan,

88
00:08:17,439 --> 00:08:18,839
can I ask you for a favor?

89
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:22,920
What is it?

90
00:08:25,519 --> 00:08:26,680
When the case is closed,

91
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:28,959
light a river lantern

92
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:30,759
for my mom

93
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:32,960
and make a wish for her.

94
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:35,320
I wish

95
00:08:36,540 --> 00:08:38,540
that she wouldn't
have to suffer anymore.

96
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:40,720
Got it.

97
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:51,120
I should've protected her.

98
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:54,879
You've done everything you could.

99
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:58,679
What happened to Tai Shu

100
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,399
wasn't your fault.

101
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:06,519
You were just a kid back then.

102
00:09:08,559 --> 00:09:09,559
Stop blaming yourself.

103
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:18,399
Su Pa, you'll be fine.

104
00:09:21,879 --> 00:09:23,759
What you did was self-defense.

105
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,120
After you go in,

106
00:09:25,519 --> 00:09:27,360
I'll get you the best lawyer.

107
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:30,120
You'll be out in no time.

108
00:09:33,639 --> 00:09:34,360
Thank you.

109
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:50,080
I wish we could go back in time.

110
00:09:53,020 --> 00:09:54,240
Back to when we were kids,

111
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:56,639
chasing after your brother,
and playing without a care.

112
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,120
We've grown up now.

113
00:10:04,980 --> 00:10:06,750
We have to learn to face things on our own.

114
00:10:15,519 --> 00:10:16,639
You can do it.

115
00:10:17,639 --> 00:10:18,639
I believe in you.

116
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:21,519
You and your brother are both amazing.

117
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:25,559
It's just a shame.

118
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,159
If only you had come back sooner.

119
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:44,240
Liao Siyuan,

120
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,759
she's our age.

121
00:10:47,879 --> 00:10:49,399
I feel so bad for her.

122
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,279
Five sixes!

123
00:11:24,799 --> 00:11:25,799
Fill her glass.

124
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:33,080
My son is calling.

125
00:11:37,583 --> 00:11:38,690
(Siyuan)

126
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:42,639
What is it, Siyuan?

127
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:44,519
You remember me now, huh?

128
00:11:46,390 --> 00:11:48,060
I'm coming home in a couple of days.

129
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:49,840
Well...

130
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:52,879
Ms. Meihua, I need a favor.

131
00:11:53,519 --> 00:11:55,720
Do you know any good nursing homes?

132
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:58,000
A nursing home?

133
00:11:59,870 --> 00:12:01,180
What, you think I'm old now?

134
00:12:01,559 --> 00:12:02,840
Trying to send me away?

135
00:12:03,919 --> 00:12:04,960
Not you.

136
00:12:06,039 --> 00:12:07,559
It's Granny Yun from Yong'an Village.

137
00:12:07,879 --> 00:12:08,879
Do you remember her?

138
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,399
Hold on.

139
00:12:18,546 --> 00:12:20,450
(Siyuan)

140
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,399
Granny Yun?

141
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:30,039
Of course, I remember her.

142
00:12:30,639 --> 00:12:32,360
The old lady who lost her sight, right?

143
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,879
Both of her sons are gone.

144
00:12:36,279 --> 00:12:37,240
She's elderly,

145
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:38,360
and blind.

146
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,519
I want to find
a good nursing home for her.

147
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:44,440
What happened to them?

148
00:12:44,799 --> 00:12:45,639
It's a long story.

149
00:12:45,910 --> 00:12:47,040
I'll explain when I see you.

150
00:12:49,759 --> 00:12:50,399
Okay.

151
00:12:51,879 --> 00:12:52,559
Siyuan,

152
00:12:52,639 --> 00:12:53,679
I'll ask around

153
00:12:53,759 --> 00:12:55,240
and see what I can find.

154
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:57,100
You stay out of trouble over there.

155
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:58,040
Come home soon.

156
00:12:59,039 --> 00:12:59,879
Wait for my update.

157
00:13:09,759 --> 00:13:12,039
AH7 wasn't the cause of Jie En's death?

158
00:13:14,399 --> 00:13:15,919
But I checked his medical records.

159
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:17,840
He didn't have
any underlying conditions.

160
00:13:19,039 --> 00:13:20,919
Okay, talk later.

161
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:25,080
Siyuan, wait for me here.

162
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:26,960
Let's go back to Buhe later
once I'm done here.

163
00:13:32,039 --> 00:13:33,759
Na Wa killed Jie En

164
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:36,320
because Jie En tried to rape Ke Xin.

165
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,159
Na Wa showed up just in time

166
00:13:38,159 --> 00:13:39,840
and shot him with a crossbow.

167
00:13:40,240 --> 00:13:41,440
When Jie En died,

168
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:43,879
he had that signature
death grin on his face.

169
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:47,960
But since the AH7 levels in his system

170
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:49,280
weren't enough to be fatal,

171
00:13:49,399 --> 00:13:50,879
there's only one explanation,

172
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:53,080
he took the AH7

173
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:54,320
after drinking.

174
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:56,840
Then, an arrow tore through his throat.

175
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,670
He lost consciousness instantly,

176
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:03,590
and his expression frozen
in that eerie smile.

177
00:14:04,559 --> 00:14:05,759
But something doesn't add up.

178
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:09,559
Jie En was drinking
and using drugs that night,

179
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,480
then he went after Ke Xin

180
00:14:12,679 --> 00:14:13,879
and got shot by Na Wa.

181
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:16,000
None of that

182
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,440
was planned by Na Wa.

183
00:14:17,759 --> 00:14:19,639
Yet, just hours after it all went down,

184
00:14:19,799 --> 00:14:21,879
Na Wa was able to come up with the idea

185
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:23,759
of faking the "River Spirit killing"

186
00:14:23,870 --> 00:14:25,420
and stage an elaborate crime scene.

187
00:14:25,860 --> 00:14:26,960
That doesn't seem possible.

188
00:14:27,919 --> 00:14:28,799
It wasn't just him.

189
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:30,120
Someone helped him.

190
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:31,879
And we've seen

191
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:33,679
this kind of setup before.

192
00:14:34,639 --> 00:14:36,399
From the Lai La case to the Nu Na case,

193
00:14:36,870 --> 00:14:39,680
he has created various bizarre
death scenes time and time again

194
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:40,870
at the hands of other people,

195
00:14:41,039 --> 00:14:43,240
exploiting people's fear of the unknown

196
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:45,000
to manufacture the illusion

197
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:46,080
of the River Spirit.

198
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:48,420
There's only one person
who could pull it off.

199
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:51,639
Bai Han.

200
00:14:52,679 --> 00:14:54,399
Yes, he must've been there.

201
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:57,039
And he arrived right before
Water Lantern Festival.

202
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:04,020
Since the Buhe police permitted
you to be involved in the case,

203
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:04,820
go ahead and watch.

204
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:05,960
Let me know when you're done.

205
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,279
Okay, thank you.

206
00:15:09,919 --> 00:15:10,559
Thanks!

207
00:15:13,679 --> 00:15:15,279
This is the only road into the village.

208
00:15:20,279 --> 00:15:21,039
It's Bai Han.

209
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:35,679
Wait.

210
00:15:37,039 --> 00:15:37,919
Who is this?

211
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:49,840
Liu Haixun.

212
00:15:51,279 --> 00:15:52,600
A businessman from Buhe.

213
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:56,360
He's also the actual owner

214
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:57,620
of Jie En's dried fruit factory.

215
00:15:59,639 --> 00:16:01,279
So he's the real boss behind the scenes.

216
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:04,559
Bai Han meeting with him here

217
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,720
wouldn't be buying dried fruit,
would he?

218
00:16:12,639 --> 00:16:13,240
Siyuan,

219
00:16:13,879 --> 00:16:15,080
get Xia to test the wastewater

220
00:16:15,150 --> 00:16:16,480
from the dried fruit factory.

221
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:18,919
Wastewater?

222
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,559
Remember we talked about

223
00:16:21,879 --> 00:16:23,679
how the river smelled different?

224
00:16:24,279 --> 00:16:27,360
Yong'an Village isn't how I remember it.

225
00:16:27,799 --> 00:16:28,799
Everything's different.

226
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:30,559
Even the smell of the river.

227
00:16:32,140 --> 00:16:33,500
There's this weird stench.

228
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:38,000
The wastewater contains
high levels of methamphetamine.

229
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:38,800
That confirms it,

230
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:40,600
it's residue from AH7 production.

231
00:16:42,879 --> 00:16:44,080
This is serious.

232
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:46,200
I need to call
the station and report it.

233
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:56,600
So they really were
using the factory as a front.

234
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:58,639
They were secretly manufacturing drugs

235
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:01,300
and using the dried fruit supply
chain to transport

236
00:17:01,399 --> 00:17:03,200
and distribute them.

237
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:07,960
Liu Haixun and Bai Han

238
00:17:09,039 --> 00:17:10,519
must have met to discuss AH7.

239
00:17:12,799 --> 00:17:14,079
Based on what we've seen before,

240
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:17,079
there's only one reason Bai Han
would be dealing with AH7,

241
00:17:17,759 --> 00:17:18,720
to kill someone.

242
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:22,359
Which means the fourth person
in that photo

243
00:17:22,820 --> 00:17:24,070
is about to come into play.

244
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:27,240
We have to find Bai Han fast

245
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:29,220
and let him to tell us
that person's identity.

246
00:17:29,280 --> 00:17:29,940
It's simple.

247
00:17:30,039 --> 00:17:31,359
We follow the shipment.

248
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:32,880
That'll take us straight to him.

249
00:17:36,697 --> 00:17:40,930
(Dried Fruit Factory)

250
00:17:57,839 --> 00:17:58,519
Great work.

251
00:18:00,039 --> 00:18:00,839
Be meticulous.

252
00:18:22,039 --> 00:18:22,720
Xun,

253
00:18:23,039 --> 00:18:24,119
go home and rest.

254
00:18:24,119 --> 00:18:25,360
I've got my eye on things here.

255
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:27,920
I need two reliable guys

256
00:18:28,519 --> 00:18:30,200
to deliver this shipment tonight.

257
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:32,200
Got it, I'll find the guys.

258
00:18:34,039 --> 00:18:35,119
No need for that trouble.

259
00:18:36,039 --> 00:18:37,920
Those two seem pretty reliable.

260
00:18:38,460 --> 00:18:39,200
I'm not going.

261
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:40,519
Why?

262
00:18:40,599 --> 00:18:42,559
They just joined us last month.

263
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:44,440
They look pretty clueless.

264
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:45,720
Perfect for this job.

265
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:49,519
Get the compensation money ready.

266
00:18:51,160 --> 00:18:51,759
Got it.

267
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:54,599
Come.

268
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:55,720
One, two, up!

269
00:18:58,279 --> 00:18:58,920
Bottom line,

270
00:18:59,110 --> 00:19:00,260
we must catch both parties

271
00:19:00,359 --> 00:19:01,880
in this drug deal.

272
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:03,079
Shu He,

273
00:19:03,319 --> 00:19:04,960
you're in charge of this operation.

274
00:19:05,519 --> 00:19:07,279
If you need a backup, call me anytime.

275
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:08,000
Yes, sir!

276
00:19:10,420 --> 00:19:11,180
Let's get to work!

277
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:11,920
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

278
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,920
Buhe police have issued
an emergency support deployment.

279
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,960
They're heading out now
and will arrive by midnight.

280
00:19:22,960 --> 00:19:23,750
It's too dangerous.

281
00:19:23,839 --> 00:19:25,000
Do not act on your own.

282
00:19:25,740 --> 00:19:26,830
Leave it to the police.

